<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1516" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1516">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.24/7–1544: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-15">July 15,
                                1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1140. Our Embassy in Montevideo reports that a serious situation in <hi rend="italic">frigoríficos</hi> may soon result from action of
                            Argentine Government in denying all export permits for shipment of salt
                            to Uruguay. Please report immediately whether there is a shortage of
                            salt in Argentina or whether we should interpret the action of the
                            Argentine Government as an economic sanction against Uruguay.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>